# Build artefacts
build/
dist/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.spec.bak

# User data — NEVER commit these
src/web/*.sqlite3
*.json.bak

# PyInstaller
*.pkg
*.pyz

# OS noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
```

**Secrets scan:** Before the first push, run `git log --all --full-history -- "*.json"` to make sure no settings files with encrypted keys accidentally got committed. Even encrypted blobs shouldn't be in a public repo's history.

---

## Repository Structure

A well-organized public repo looks like this:
```
EmuHub/
├── src/
│   ├── main.py
│   └── web/
│       └── index.html
├── assets/
│   └── icon.ico
├── screenshots/          ← add these
│   ├── library.png
│   ├── settings.png
│   └── launch.png
├── .gitignore
├── LICENSE
├── README.md
├── BUILD.bat
├── RUN_DEV.bat
├── EmuHub.spec
└── version_info.txt
